{"title_page": "Tap4Fun", "text_new": "{{Notability|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Tap4Fun\n| image               = T4F_company-logo.jpg\n| industry            = [[Video game industry|Video games]]\n| founded             = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2008}}\n| founder             = Yang 'Kevin' Xiangji\n| hq_location_city    = [[Chengdu]]\n| hq_location_country = China\n| area_served         = Worldwide\n| key_people          = {{Unbulleted list|Yang 'Kevin' Xiangji ([[chairman]])|Xu 'Stan' Zizhan ([[Chief executive officer|CEO]])}}\n| num_employees       = 800\n| num_employees_year  = 2016\n| website             = {{URL|http://www.tap4fun.com/|tap4fun.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Tap4fun Co., Ltd.''' operates as a mobile online games development company. The Company offers mobile online games designing, development, operating, marketing, and other services. Tap4fun provides services worldwide.<ref name=\"corporate\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profile/company/1278691D:CH |title=tap4fun company page |website=bloomberg}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n\ntap4fun (Chengdu Nibirutech Inc) was founded in March, 2008 and is located in Chengdu Tianfu Software Park Zone A, with main business on the development, distribution and operation of SLG mobile game. It's a joint-stock company transformed from Chengdu Nibirutech Ltd. which has published 9 games and has being the voice of China in the international mobile game market. Currently, the main business of the company focuses on developing, operating and investing mobile online games. Sticking to the faith of developing quality games, the company, dedicated to mobile games development, produced 9 games such as Invasion, Brutal Age, Galaxy Legend and Spartan Wars.\n\nIn March 2012, Galactic Empire topped the App store of United States; In April 2012, the King's Empire topped the App store of China. According to the 2012 global mobile game enterprises income list issued by App Annie the third party of international authority, tap4fun has been listed in the top 50 where there were only 2 Chinese enterprises been listed. And according to the 2014 Fastest-Growing Technology Companies issued by Deloitte, tap4fun was the No.1 of the top 20 of Chengdu city, and was the 3rd of the top 50 in China.\n\nIn 2015, Invasion was honored the best mobile game of the world by Facebook, and tap4fun published prospectus and plan to be on the main board of Shanghai stock exchange in the same year. On May 16, 2016, tap4fun was the only game company that was invited to the 8th China Trip of Tim Cook, the CEO of Apple company. On January 10, 2017, tap4fun was listed the 19th of the top 30 China brands issued by BrandZ, the consultant company of the biggest global media group WPP.<ref name=\"tap50\">{{cite web |url=https://pandaily.com/facebook-releases-list-of-top-50-chinese-brands-with-great-global-influences/ |title=Top50 chinese brands |website=pandaily |accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Studios ==\n\n* Tap4fun Headquarters (Chengdu)\n* Tap4fun Co., Ltd. (HongKong)\n* Tap4fun (Beijing)\n* Tap4fun (Paris)\n* Tap4fun (Thailand) Ltd.\n\n== Games ==\n\n* Kiss of War\n* Sea Game\n* Brutal Age\n* Invasion\n* Galaxy Legend\n* Royal Empire\n* Spartan Wars\n* King's Empire\n* Galaxy Empire\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/company/tap4fun/about/\n\nhttps://tap4fun.com/story\n\nhttps://www.send2press.com/wire/tap4fun-launches-an-invasion-with-new-3d-battle-strategy-action-game-for-ios-and-android-2015-0710-02/\n\n[[Category:Mobile game companies]]\n[[Category:Video game development companies]]\n[[Category:Video game publishers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Notability|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Tap4Fun\n| image               = T4F_company-logo.jpg\n| industry            = [[Video game industry|Video games]]\n| founded             = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2008}}\n| founder             = Yang 'Kevin' Xiangji\n| hq_location_city    = [[Chengdu]]\n| hq_location_country = China\n| area_served         = Worldwide\n| key_people          = {{Unbulleted list|Yang 'Kevin' Xiangji ([[chairman]])|Xu 'Stan' Zizhan ([[Chief executive officer|CEO]])}}\n| num_employees       = 800\n| num_employees_year  = 2016\n| website             = {{URL|http://www.tap4fun.com/|tap4fun.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Tap4fun Co., Ltd.''' operates as a mobile online games development company. The Company offers mobile online games designing, development, operating, marketing, and other services. Tap4fun provides services worldwide<ref name=\"corporate\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profile/company/1278691D:CH |title=tap4fun company page |website=bloomberg}}</ref>.\n\n== History ==\n\ntap4fun (Chengdu Nibirutech Inc) was founded in March, 2008 and is located in Chengdu Tianfu Software Park Zone A, with main business on the development, distribution and operation of SLG mobile game. It's a joint-stock company transformed from Chengdu Nibirutech Ltd. which has published 9 games and has being the voice of China in the international mobile game market. Currently, the main business of the company focuses on developing, operating and investing mobile online games. Sticking to the faith of developing quality games, the company, dedicated to mobile games development, produced 9 games such as Invasion, Brutal Age, Galaxy Legend and Spartan Wars. \n\nIn March 2012, Galactic Empire topped the App store of United States; In April 2012, the King\u2019s Empire topped the App store of China. According to the 2012 global mobile game enterprises income list issued by App Annie the third party of international authority, tap4fun has been listed in the top 50 where there were only 2 Chinese enterprises been listed. And according to the 2014 Fastest-Growing Technology Companies issued by Deloitte, tap4fun was the No.1 of the top 20 of Chengdu city, and was the 3rd of the top 50 in China. \n\nIn 2015, Invasion was honored the best mobile game of the world by Facebook, and tap4fun published prospectus and plan to be on the main board of Shanghai stock exchange in the same year. On May 16, 2016, tap4fun was the only game company that was invited to the 8th China Trip of Tim Cook, the CEO of Apple company. On January 10, 2017, tap4fun was listed the 19th of the top 30 China brands issued by BrandZ, the consultant company of the biggest global media group WPP<ref name=\"tap50\">{{cite web |url=https://pandaily.com/facebook-releases-list-of-top-50-chinese-brands-with-great-global-influences/ |title=Top50 chinese brands |website=pandaily |accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref>.\n\n== Studios ==\n\n* Tap4fun Headquarters (Chengdu)\n* Tap4fun Co., Ltd. (HongKong)\n* Tap4fun (Beijing)\n* Tap4fun (Paris)\n* Tap4fun (Thailand) Ltd.\n\n== Games ==\n\n* Kiss of War\n* Sea Game\n* Brutal Age\n* Invasion\n* Galaxy Legend\n* Royal Empire\n* Spartan Wars\n* King's Empire\n* Galaxy Empire\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/company/tap4fun/about/\n\nhttps://tap4fun.com/story\n\nhttps://www.send2press.com/wire/tap4fun-launches-an-invasion-with-new-3d-battle-strategy-action-game-for-ios-and-android-2015-0710-02/\n[[Category:Mobile game companies]]\n[[Category:Video game development companies]]\n[[Category:Video game publishers]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tap4Fun"}
