r)|Alan Grant]], [[John Wagner]] and [[Val Semeiks]] (Abril Jovem)\n*1999: ''O Sistema'' (''The System'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Peter Kuper]] (Abril Jovem)\n*2000: ''Tex Gigante'' #1: ''Tex - o homem de Atlanta'' (''[[Tex Willer|Tex Albo Speciale (Texone)]]'' #10) {{flagicon|ITA}}, by [[Claudio Nizzi]] and [[Jordi Bernet]] (Mythos)\n*2001: ''Palestina - uma na\u00e7\u00e3o ocupada'' (''[[Palestine (comics)|Palestine]]'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Joe Sacco]] (Conrad)\n*2002: ''Gorazde - \u00e1rea de seguran\u00e7a'' (''[[Safe Area Gora\u017ede]]'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Joe Sacco]] (Conrad)\n*2003: ''A Paix\u00e3o do Arlequim'' (''[[Harlequin Valentine]]''), {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Neil Gaiman]] and [[John Bolton (illustrator)|John Bolton]] (Conrad)\n\n=== Best Foreign Miniseries ===\nThe award considers the Brazilian edition of the works.\n*1989: ''Elektra assassina'' (''[[Elektra: Assassin]]'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Frank Miller (comics)|Frank Miller]] and [[Bill Sienkiewicz]] (Abril)\n*1990: ''Orqu\u00eddea Negra'' (''[[Black Orchid (comics)|Black Orchid]]'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Neil Gaiman]] and [[Dave McKean]] (Abril Jovem)\n*1991: ''V de Vingan\u00e7a'' (''[[V for Vendetta]]'') {{flagicon|GBR}}, by [[Alan Moore]] and [[David Lloyd (comics)|David Lloyd]] (Globo)\n*1992: ''Os Livros da Magia'' (''[[The Books of Magic]]'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Neil Gaiman]] and many pencillers (Abril Jovem)\n*1993: ''Batman/Juiz Dredd - julgamento em Gotham'' (''[[Batman/Judge Dredd: Judgment on Gotham]]'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Alan Grant (writer)|Alan Grant]], [[John Wagner]] and [[Simon Bisley]] (Abril Jovem)\n*1994: ''Batman - a espada de Azrael'' (''[[Azrael (comics)|Batman: Sword of Azrael]]'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Denny O'Neil]] e [[Joe Quesada]] (Abril Jovem)\n*1995: ''Lobo est\u00e1 morto'' (''Lobo's Back'') {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Keith Giffen]], [[Alan Grant (writer)|Alan Grant]] and [[Simon Bisley]] (Abril Jovem)\n*1996: ''[[Marvels]]'' {{flagicon|USA}}, by [[Ku