alon, in 1973 in Col\u00e9gio Mackenzie)\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Trof\u00e9u HQ Mix winners}}\n[[Category:Brazilian comics]]\n[[Category:Brazilian awards]]\n[[Category:Comics awards]]\n[[Category:Comics-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of award winners]]\n", "name_user": "Lucio Luiz", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBest Webcomic", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Trof%C3%A9u_HQ_Mix_winners"}
{"title_page": "DECA Games", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Deca Games O\u00dc\n| logo             = \n| logo_size        = 200px\n| type = \n| location = [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]]\n| key_people = \n| industry = [[Video game industry|Video games]]\n| products = \n| revenue =\n| operating_income =\n| net_income =\n| num_employees = \n| parent = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{URL|https://decagames.com/}}\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''DECA Games O\u00dc''' is a publisher and developer of video games that are headquartered in [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]]. They are known for being the current owners and developers of the [[Adobe Flash|Flash]] game, [[Realm of the Mad God]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2019-10-28-one-companys-cast-off-can-be-deca-games-treasure|title=One company's cast-off can be Deca Games' treasure|website=GamesIndustry.biz}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/08/17/deca-games-uses-live-operations-to-breathe-life-into-old-games/|title=Kabam vet leads Deca Games\u2019 charge into live operations for old games|date=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The company has also acquired a number of free-to-play mobile games, including [[DragonVale]] and multiple titles from Japanese publisher [[GREE]] (including Crime City, Knights and Dragons, Modern War and Kingdom Age).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/359705/Deca_Games_acquires_DragonVale_following_Backflip_Studios_closure.php|title=Deca Games acquires DragonVale following Backflip Studios closure|first=Alissa|last=McAloon|website=www.gamasutra.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/news/71804/deca-games-f2p-long-tail-buying-one-time-hits-gree/|title=Deca Games plays F2P\u2019s long tail, buying 4 one-time hits from GREE|first1=Jon|last1=Jordan|first2=Contributing|last2=Editor|website=pocketgamer.biz}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Deca Games O\u00dc\n| logo             = \n| logo_size        = 200px\n| type = \n| location = [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]]\n| key_people = \n| industry = [[Video game industry|Video games]]\n| products = \n| revenue =\n| operating_income =\n| net_income =\n| num_employees = \n| parent = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{URL|https://decagames.com/}}\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''DECA Games O\u00dc''' is a publisher and developer of video games that are headquartered in [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]]. They are known for being the current owners and developers of the [[Adobe Flash|Flash]] game, [[Realm of the Mad God]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2019-10-28-one-companys-cast-off-can-be-deca-games-treasure|title=One company's cast-off can be Deca Games' treasure|website=GamesIndustry.biz}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/08/17/deca-games-uses-live-operations-to-breathe-life-into-old-games/|title=Kabam vet leads Deca Games\u2019 charge into live operations for old games|date=August 17, 2017}}</ref> The company has also acquired a number of free-to-play mobile games, including [[DragonVale]] and multiple titles from Japanese publisher [[GREE]] (including Crime City, Knights and Dragons, Modern War and Kingdom Age).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/359705/Deca_Games_acquires_DragonVale_following_Backflip_Studios_closure.php|title=Deca Games acquires DragonVale following Backflip Studios closure|first=Alissa|last=McAloon|website=www.gamasutra.com}}</ref><ref>https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/news/71804/deca-games-f2p-long-tail-buying-one-time-hits-gree/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{stub}}\n", "name_user": "Liance", "label": "safe", "comment": "Filled in 1 bare reference(s) with reFill 2", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DECA_Games"}
